# Pulse Environment Variables
# This file is automatically generated during deployment
# Copy this to .env and customize if needed

# DNS Configuration
# This file is automatically generated from terraform.tfvars during deployment
# Required for Pulse to resolve Proxmox hostnames on your internal network
# IMPORTANT: Use your DNS server on the monitoring network (10.200.10.0/24)
DNS_SERVER1=10.200.10.1
DNS_SERVER2=
DNS_DOMAIN=yourdomain.local
DNS_SEARCH=yourdomain.local

# Proxmox Nodes Information (for reference only)
# Pulse will auto-discover these nodes on your network
# You can also configure nodes manually through the Pulse web interface at http://<your-ip>:7655

# Example nodes on monitoring network (10.200.10.10-13):
# PROXMOX_NODE1=proxmox1.yourdomain.local (10.200.10.10)
# PROXMOX_NODE2=proxmox2.yourdomain.local (10.200.10.11)
# PROXMOX_NODE3=proxmox3.yourdomain.local (10.200.10.12)
# PROXMOX_NODE4=proxmox4.yourdomain.local (10.200.10.13)

# Notes:
# - Pulse automatically discovers Proxmox nodes on your network
# - Configure authentication (API tokens) through the Pulse web interface
# - No need to store sensitive credentials in this file
# - Pulse stores all configuration in its persistent data volume: /data
